fields.name: Process sequence ID
fields.description: This is a custom field with values provided in the template.

fields.name: Catalog Status
fields.description: This field can help you track the status of the row in the business process catalog when Microsoft publishes new versions.

fields.name: Story Points
fields.description: The size of work estimated for fixing the bug

fields.name: Remaining Work
fields.description: An estimate of the number of units of work remaining to complete this bug

fields.name: Original Estimate
fields.description: Initial value for Remaining Work - set once, when work begins

fields.name: Completed Work
fields.description: The number of units of work that have been spent on this bug

fields.name: Activity
fields.description: Type of work involved

fields.name: System Info
fields.description: Test context, provided automatically by test infrastructure

fields.name: Repro Steps
fields.description: How to see the bug. End by contrasting expected with actual behavior.

fields.name: Resolved Reason
fields.description: The reason why the bug was resolved

fields.name: Severity
fields.description: Assessment of the effect of the bug on the project

fields.name: Stack Rank
fields.description: Work first on items with lower-valued stack rank. Set in triage.

fields.name: Value Area
fields.description: The type should be set to Business primarily to represent customer-facing issues. Work to change the architecture should be added as a User Story

fields.name: Integration Build
fields.description: The build in which the bug was fixed

fields.name: Found In
fields.description: The build in which the bug was found

fields.name: Target Date
fields.description: The target date for completing the epic

fields.name: Start Date
fields.description: The date to start the task

fields.name: Application Type
fields.description: The type of application on which to give feedback

fields.name: Application Start Information
fields.description: The path to execute the application

fields.name: Application Launch Instructions
fields.description: Instructions to launch the specified application

fields.name: Rating
fields.description: Overall rating provided as part of feedback response

fields.name: Issue
fields.description: Used to highlight the shared step, e.g., to mark it as an issue

fields.name: Steps
fields.description: Steps required to perform the test

fields.name: Finish Date
fields.description: The date to finish the task

fields.name: Automated Test Name
fields.description: The name of the test that automates this test case

fields.name: Automated Test Storage
fields.description: The assembly containing the test that automates this test case

fields.name: Automated Test Id
fields.description: The ID of the test that automates this test case

fields.name: Automated Test Type
fields.description: The type of the test that automates this test case

fields.name: Test Suite Type
fields.description: Specifies the category of the test suite.

fields.name: Test Suite Audit
fields.description: Captures the test suite audit trail.

fields.name: Due Date
fields.description: The date by which this issue needs to be closed

workItemTypes.name: Workshop
workItemTypes.description: Stores detailed information about how to run a workshop.

workItemTypes.name: Scenario
workItemTypes.description: Groups all work items related to patterns (Level 4 in the catalog) within a business process.

workItemTypes.name: Configuration deliverable
workItemTypes.description: Configuration deliverables represent setup or configuration that is required in Dynamics 365 to support one or more processes

workItemTypes.name: Process
workItemTypes.description: Groups all work items related to business processes (Level 3 in the catalog) within each business process area.

workItemTypes.name: Collection
workItemTypes.description: Group all work items related to end-to-end processes.

workItemTypes.name: End to end
workItemTypes.description: Groups all work items related to end-to-end processes (Level 1 in the catalog).

workItemTypes.name: Process area
workItemTypes.description: Groups all work items related to business process areas (Level 2 in the catalog) within the different end-to-end processes

workItemTypes.name: Document deliverable
workItemTypes.description: A placeholder for a document such as a design document, statement of work, or other documentation for the project.
